From 0158a20b54aa4c2c62f03d27c5546b99a8492726 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 14:58:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Kapework analytics hooks and first-interaction tracking
 to games

### Motivation
- Add consistent analytics instrumentation across multiple browser games to capture run lifecycle, first user interactions, and primary actions for product telemetry.

### Description
- Introduce shared helper functions `analytics()`, `trackFirstInteraction()`, `trackRunStart()`, `trackRunEnd()`, and `trackPrimaryAction()` to `tapsum/game.js`, `tiltgarden.html` (embedded script), and `tiltrix/game.js` and wire them to `window.KapeworkAnalytics` safely.
- Call `trackRunStart()` when a run/session/game starts and include a `source` parameter such as `initial_load`, `start_button`, or `play_again` by updating `startRun`, `startSession`, and `startGame` signatures and invocation sites.
- Call `trackRunEnd()` at run/session/game completion with summary payloads (e.g. `score`, `boards_cleared`, `exact_hits`, `best_chain`, `lives_left`, `outcome` for `tapsum`; `placed`/`lines` for `tiltgarden`; `score`/`lines`/`round` for `tiltrix`).
- Instrument first user interactions across input paths by calling `trackFirstInteraction()` on the first meaningful input actions such as `tap`, `move`, `rotate`, `drop`, `settle`, `lean`, and `tilt`.
- Add calls to `trackPrimaryAction()` for obvious primary actions like `play_again` and `share` in button handlers.
- Move the `tiltrix` game script include to the bottom of the HTML to match other pages and ensure `KapeworkAnalytics.init()`/shell initialization runs before the game script.

### Testing
- Ran linters and a local build with `npm run lint` and `npm run build`, both completed successfully.
- Verified through a local smoke run that instrumented functions guard against missing `window.KapeworkAnalytics` (no runtime errors occurred when analytics was absent).
- Existing automated CI (if present) should run unchanged test suites; no new unit tests were added in this PR.
